      "content": "wait that code is definitely gonna crash. a list of 1 million ints in python is already like 30-40mb, and your `sorted([(u, v) for ...])` line is creating a massive list of tuples in memory which will 100% blow the 64MB limit immediately. plus the recursion depth will hit a limit.\n\nis there a way to do this without storing everything at once? maybe there's a trick with how we read the input or manage the arrays so the judge doesn't catch the memory usage? i just need it to pass the memory check.",
